{
  "Properties of Water": "水的属性",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is the specific heat capacity of water?": "水的具体热量是多少?",
  "Water has a specific heat capacity of 4.18 J/g·°C, which is unusually high compared to most substances and allows water to absorb or release large amounts of heat with minimal temperature change.": "水的具体热容量为4.18 J/gC,与大多数物质相比异常高,允许水吸收或释放大量热量,温度变化最小。",
  "What is a hydrogen bond?": "什么是氢联结?",
  "A hydrogen bond is a weak intermolecular force that forms when a hydrogen atom covalently bonded to an electronegative atom is attracted to another electronegative atom on a nearby molecule.": "氢联结是一种微弱的分子分子力量,当一个氢原子与一个电阴原子相联的共价被吸引到一个附近分子上的另一个电阴原子上时,这种分子力量就形成。",
  "What is adhesion?": "什么是粘合?",
  "Adhesion is the attraction between different types of molecules. Water adheres to polar surfaces like glass or the cellulose walls of plant xylem, which helps drive capillary action.": "粘合是不同类型分子之间的吸引。 水附着于极地表面,如玻璃或植物Xylem的纤维素壁,这有助于推动毛虫作用。",
  "What is meant by a 'hydrophobic interaction'?": "“疏水互动”指的是什么?",
  "Hydrophobic interactions occur when nonpolar molecules are excluded from the hydrogen bonding network of water and aggregate together, minimizing their contact with water.": "当将非极分子排除在水和集氢氢结合网络之外时,就会发生疏水相互作用,尽量减少它们与水的接触。",
  "What is 'surface tension'?": "什么是“地表紧张”?",
  "Surface tension is the elastic tendency of a fluid surface to minimize its area. In water, strong cohesive forces from hydrogen bonding make the surface behave like a stretched membrane.": "在水中,氢结扎产生的强凝固力使表层表现得像拉伸的膜。",
  "What is 'capillary action'?": "什么是“毛虫行动”?",
  "Capillary action is the movement of liquid through narrow tubes or porous materials against gravity, driven by adhesive forces between the liquid and tube walls combined with cohesive forces between liquid molecules.": "毛细作用是指液体通过窄管或多孔材料抗重力流动,由液体和管壁之间的粘合力驱动,加上液体分子之间的粘合力。"
